articles.description: Desmond Williams scored 16 of his 21 points in the second half and Florida A&M held off North Carolina Central 65-56 on Saturday night.
articles.headline: Florida A&M beats North Carolina Central 65-56

articles.description: Ken'Darrius Hamilton and Delano Spencer scored 15 apiece and Hamilton added seven rebounds to lead Tennessee State to a 65-47 victory over Jacksonville State on Saturday night.
articles.headline: Tennessee State turns back Jacksonville State 65-47

articles.description: Jordan Caroline scored 26 points and Lindsay Drew just missed a triple-double with 12 points, 11 rebounds and nine assists in No. 23 Nevada's 83-58 victory over San Diego State on Saturday night.
articles.headline: No. 23 Nevada beats San Diego State 83-58

articles.description: Dimencio Vaughn scored 28 points and grabbed a dozen rebounds as Rider staged an improbable comeback, roaring back from 21 points down in the final 10 minutes to post an 89-79 win over Marist Saturday to maintain a share of first place in the Metro...
articles.headline: Rider holds onto MAAC lead, rallies past Marist, 89-79

articles.description: Taylor Johnson scored 21 points and Dartmouth picked up its first conference win, downing Princeton 72-56 on Saturday night, snapping a 10-game skid.
articles.headline: Dartmouth downs Princeton 72-56

images.caption: Big Green holds off Princeton to pick up its first #RoadtoIvyMadness victory of the year
images.name: Dartmouth picks up first Ivy win of the season  - Via Ivy League

articles.description: Nick Mayo scored 18 points, grabbed five rebounds and blocked four shots and Eastern Kentucky made 4 of 6 foul shots down the stretch to hold off Morehead State 75-73 on Saturday night.
articles.headline: E. Kentucky holds off Morehead St.; Mayo scores 18 PTs

videos.description: Charles Matthews hits the 3-pointer off the bank just before the shot clock expires for Michigan.
videos.headline: Matthews beats shot clock with bank-shot 3-pointer

videos.description: Michigan's Muhammad-Ali Abdur-Rahkman gets by several North Carolina defenders for the finger roll layup.
videos.headline: Abdur-Rahkman slashes through defenders

videos.description: Duncan Robinson misses the layup on the front of the rim and North Carolina takes the rebound up the court for the Theo Pinson layup.
videos.headline: Missed basket leads to Pinson reverse layup

videos.description: Off the pass from Joel Berry II, Luke Maye hits the 3-pointer.
videos.headline: Maye knocks down 3-pointer from top of arc

videos.description: Michigan head coach John Beilein was disappointed with his team allowing North Carolina to go into halftime with a big lead.
videos.headline: Beilein claims Michigan has to play better team basketball

videos.description: Luke Maye hands it off to Garrison Brooks underneath the basket who makes the dunk plus the foul.
videos.headline: Brooks throws down dunk and-1

videos.description: Luke Maye gets by Michigan defenders and absorbs contact for the layup and foul.
videos.headline: Maye drives for the layup and the foul

videos.description: Luke Maye drives the baseline and gets the reverse layup to go and the foul.
videos.headline: Maye with another and-1 off the reverse layup

videos.description: Luke Maye scores a game-high 27 points and Joel Berry II adds 17 to carry North Carolina past Michigan 86-71.
videos.headline: Maye, Berry lead UNC past Michigan
